SIMPLE: unman
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unman
<hw>Un*man"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>man</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To deprive of the distinctive qualities of a human
being, as reason, or the like.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To emasculate; to deprive of virility.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To deprive of the courage and fortitude of a man; to
break or subdue the manly spirit in; to cause to despond; to dishearten;
to make womanish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let's not <qex>unman</qex> each other.</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To deprive of men; <as>as, to <ex>unman</ex> a
ship</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unmanacle</ent>⟦br⟧
